channel.title: [Pi] Two Errors [Pi]
channel.description:
Hey guys, I'm trying to add Region clipping to my server so I had to add a Region.java, I had about 20 errors that I fixed when I first got it but I've gotten it down to only two, but I cannot fix them, the compiler is saying the the Region file cannot find ObjectDef, but I'm not even sure what ObjectDef is supposed to be so does anybody know if I need to add anything or get rid of this or just change something?
[code]src\server\model\players\Region.java:214: cannot find symbol symbol : class ObjectDef location: class server.model.players.Region ObjectDef def = ObjectDef.getObjectDef(objectId); ^ src\server\model\players\Region.java:214: cannot find symbol symbol : variable ObjectDef location: class server.model.players.Region ObjectDef def = ObjectDef.getObjectDef(objectId); ^ Note: Some input files use unchecked or unsafe operations. Note: Recompile with -Xlint:unchecked for details. 2 errors Press any key to continue . . .[/code]

item.title: [Pi] Two Errors [Pi]
item.dc:creator: @Scape-JAVA Scape-JAVA
item.description:
@Scape-JAVA wrote:

You need to import the ObjectDef class, if you don’t have one that’s why it’s printing the error out because there is no variable defined/no ObjectDef subclass to be extended or imported.

Try looking into inheritance, it may help you with future endeavors within programming.
